This paper deals with the problem of offloading in femtocaching-assisted cellular networks, which involves optimizing the transmission of data between the macrocell base station and the femtocaches. This problem is related to several areas of computer science, including network coding (cs.NI), information theory (cs.IT), distributed computing (cs.DC), systems and control (cs.SY), and multimedia (cs.MM). However, given the focus on wireless networks and optimization, we believe that cs.NI and cs.IT are the most likely categories, followed by cs.DC, cs.SY, and cs.MM.
